HEADWORD: Heteracanth
<hw>Het"er*a*canth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a spine.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the spines of the dorsal fin unsymmetrical, or thickened
alternately on the right and left sides.</def>⟦br⟧
